user.biography: Showing you how to build a beautiful home on a budget with power tools in one hand and toddlers in the other.  Let’s do this! 🔨🏠

node.text: Operation guest room transplant: complete! 😁✅. If I didn’t live 11 doors down from my mom, this would totally be where I stayed😂. I used all of my old guest room furniture that never got used and gave it to my mom to turn her guest room into a dream😍 I know I called this wall color “bold” (and for me it is 🤣) but I LOVE it so much!! The perfect dusty rose (or adult pink)😍 PS - my mom loves it 😘

node.text: I have a LINEN CLOSET!! 🤩  For the last 4 years I’ve lived without any linen closets in our house so I finally took matters into my own hands and BUILT ONE!  I took this unused dead corner in the back of our house and turned it into functional storage using 3 pre made cabinets! 👊🏼 This took me just 2.5 days and wasn’t too hard!  Are you going to try it??😍

node.text:
Who knew a PANTRY could look this good!🤩 I neglected this space for yearssss because “it’s just a closet and nobody ever sees it” but you know who sees it EVERY DAY? ME! (Because oreos, not bc I cook🤣) And you know who LOVES IT now?! 🙋🏻‍♀️ I am obsessed with this 4x4 space and it’s complete with all my favorite finishes that are so ME! I realized while doing this pantry that A LOT of us have these corner pantry closets complete with builder wire shelving and I hope I’ve given you the confidence and inspiration that it doesn’t have to be that way ❤️😘
.
.

#diy #pantry #beforeandafter #organization #kitchendecor #pantrygoals #pantryorganization #pantrymakeover

node.text:
The built in pantry of my dreams is halfway done!!😍. I had a heck of a time getting that countertop in today, but I fought hard and didn’t let it win💪🏼. And the seam turned out pretty darn good, too!  Swipe to see what my pantry looked like last week!  I used mostly scraps to build these shelves and I’m so anxious to finish it!  If you think it’s good now, just waittttt to see what I add next 🥰 
(My pantry is roughly 4x4 and the paint color is boothbay gray)

node.text: WE DID IT 🤩 My neighbors bedroom is done! And y’all helped me design every single part 🤗. Was this super fun or what?? They trusted us to give their bedroom a much needed makeover (swipe!) and I think it turned out pretty darn good, don’t you??😍. I think the show stopping @generationlighting chandelier from @lighting_design_company is my favorite part!! We need to do this again I think 😂

node.text: Holy cow those beams though!!😍 and since they went up so fast we got the window trim and bed done too!! Isn’t it cool to see the room we digitally designed together come to life?! These beams aren’t going anywhere since I used @theoriginalsuperglue Total Tech to secure the cleats to the ceiling!  It’s strong adhesive and fast drying properties made it a breeze!  Who’s ready to hang their own faux beams??😍 #sponsored

node.text: It’s NAVY SHIPLAP y’all 🤩. And I adore it!! But more importantly, so do my neighbors!! Swipe to see their bedroom before and how far we’ve already come!  The design you all voted on is coming together one week at a time and it’s so freaking fun!! And thank you for believing that I had a master plan for why I didn’t paint all of the grooves first 🤣 that was a blast!  Do you love it?!

node.text: Ikea dresser hack DONE!🤗. What do you think about this MASSIVE 9 drawer dresser made from three ikea malm chests? Isn’t it the coolest?? And talk about storage for days! 😍. This was a really inexpensive way to get a large dresser for my neighbors bedroom makeover and I’m excited to see how many of you try it!  Are you happy we went with navy?😍

node.text: 🎉Happy Birthday🎉 to my army loving camo wearing boy!❤️. He is FIVE!  Five years being a mama and still finding it so wild to see a miniature version of yourself walking around complete with all your quirks 🙃. I love this boy to the moon and we had an amazing day celebrating him with our favorite people ❤️🇺🇸

node.text:
My best friend’s bedroom is done!! {swipe!} Culton helped me turn his parents room into a magazine worthy retreat and I hope they love it half as much as I do! 😅 The simple things are what made the biggest impact in this space: PAINT, new baseboards and trimmed out the windows!  I upcycled half a headboard to create this bed, and reused the fan and curtain rods from my old bedroom to finish off this space!  I can’t get over the before and after, can you?! 😍
.
.
.
.
.
